oc:kn_123823f7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing sampling rate and crop duration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use 2048 Hz sampling for standard binary mergers; use 4096 Hz for high-mass systems needing better time-resolution. Crop minimum 2 seconds from each end, more for longer templates." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Higher sampling rates increase computational cost; adequate cropping removes edge artifacts that cause false triggers" .

oc:kn_2601dce6 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When estimating PSD for matched filtering" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The PSD low-frequency cutoff must match the high-pass filter cutoff frequency (typically 15 Hz). Data must be long enough after cropping to support multiple Welch segments." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mismatched cutoffs lead to poorly characterized noise at low frequencies; insufficient data causes Welch method to fail" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_41e4ed38 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When conditioning raw gravitational wave strain data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. High-pass filter at 15 Hz to remove low-frequency noise 2. Resample to 2048 Hz (or 4096 Hz) to reduce computational cost 3. Crop 2+ seconds from both ends to remove filter wraparound artifacts 4. Estimate PSD via Welch's method (4s segments), interpolate, apply inverse spectrum truncation" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This order prevents aliasing during resampling and ensures clean PSD estimation for matched filtering" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_47173089 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When ordering the conditioning pipeline steps" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never resample before high-pass filtering — resampling without prior filtering causes aliasing of low-frequency noise into the band of interest" ;
    oc:hasRationale "Aliasing irreversibly corrupts the signal band, degrading matched filtering SNR" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_57643b3a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "On PSD estimation failure or poor matched filtering results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If PSD estimation fails with 'must contain at least one sample', ensure data is long enough after cropping. If filter wraparound artifacts appear in matched filtering, increase crop amount or verify filtering preceded cropping. If poor SNR persists, increase high-pass cutoff or check inverse spectrum truncation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the most common conditioning failures and each has a targeted fix" .

oc:kn_5cdae13b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "PyCBC must be installed (pip install pycbc). Input must be a PyCBC TimeSeries object." .

oc:kn_c4a2b637 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting sampling rate" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Resampling from original detector rate to 2048 Hz significantly reduces computational cost of downstream matched filtering. 4096 Hz doubles data volume vs 2048 Hz." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Downsampling is the primary computational optimization in the conditioning pipeline" .

oc:kn_cf588aca a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Complete conditioning pipeline from raw strain to PSD-ready data" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """from pycbc.filter import highpass, resample_to_delta_t
from pycbc.psd import interpolate, inverse_spectrum_truncation

strain_filtered = highpass(strain, 15.0)
strain_resampled = resample_to_delta_t(strain_filtered, 1.0/2048)
conditioned = strain_resampled.crop(2, 2)
psd = conditioned.psd(4)
psd = interpolate(psd, conditioned.delta_f)
psd = inverse_spectrum_truncation(psd, int(4 * conditioned.sample_rate), low_frequency_cutoff=15)""" .

